Privacy Policy
Last updated: 29 March, 2025

This Privacy Policy governs your use of the QR Scanner & Barcode Reader application (hereafter referred to as "the App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a secure user experience.

1. Data Collection
We do not collect any personal or non-personal information from users. The App is designed to function without requiring any personally identifiable information (PII).

2. Third-Party Services
The App may use Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob may collect certain data, such as:

Device information (e.g., model, OS version)

Location data (if enabled)

App usage data

We do not have access to this information. For details on how AdMob handles your data, please review Googleâ€™s Privacy Policy.

3. Permissions
The App may request the following permissions:

Camera Access: Used only for scanning QR codes and barcodes. No images or data are stored.

Storage Access (Optional): Required if you choose to save generated QR codes on your device.

These permissions are solely for app functionality and are not used for data collection.

4. Data Usage
As we do not collect or store any data, your information remains private. Any data collected through third-party services like AdMob is used only for advertising purposes in accordance with their policies.

5. Data Sharing
We do not share, sell, or rent any user data. However, third-party services such as AdMob may share limited data for personalized advertising as outlined in their privacy policies.

6. Security
Although we do not collect personal data, we take necessary security measures to ensure the App provides a safe and secure experience.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe that a child has provided information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this privacy policy periodically. Any changes will be reflected with the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage users to review this policy regularly.

